<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-09T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-09T19:00:00-05:00" n="327" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/12517a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-09T19:00:00-05:00">December 9, 1918—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>6579. Associated Press on November 12, 1918, reported under Paris date a
                            despatch of the Frankfort <hi rend="italic">Gazette</hi> in Budapest
                            that the new <pb facs="0485" n="397" xml:id="pg_397"/> Roumanian
                            Government had declared war on Germany. Please ascertain if it is a fact
                            that the Roumanian Government has declared war on Germany, and whether
                            the French Government now regards Roumania as at war with Germany on the
                            side of the Allies.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>